726773f-a.text:
Grand Avenue, at the N.E. corner of 68th Street (left extending north), showing in fouu views at the corner,the home of Judge William Burcham in 1872 which was demolished in Jure 1925. It is said that this house is on the site of the John Firth house of 1850. One Dovle was an occupant of the house seen in these views. View No. four shows a rear of the house viewed across the B.R.T. tracks parallelking
Borden Avenue.
February 1924
